  "prompt": "What are the different grade levels and titles at Deloitte Consulting US?",
  "response": "Deloitte Consulting US typically has a structured hierarchy, which can vary slightly depending on the specific service line or practice area. However, the general grade levels and titles include:\n\n1. **Analyst**: Entry-level position for recent graduates or those with limited experience. Analysts typically assist with research, analysis, and the implementation of projects.\n\n2. **Consultant**: After gaining experience as an Analyst, individuals are promoted to Consultant. Consultants take on more responsibility for project work, client interactions, and may lead small teams.\n\n3. **Senior Consultant**: With additional experience and demonstrated performance, Consultants are promoted to Senior Consultant. Senior Consultants often manage larger components of projects and may oversee the work of Analysts and Consultants.\n\n4. **Manager**: Managers are responsible for leading entire projects, managing client relationships, and ensuring the delivery of high-quality work. They also play a role in business development and may mentor junior staff.\n\n5. **Senior Manager**: Senior Managers have significant experience and are responsible for managing complex projects, leading multiple teams, and contributing to strategic business development initiatives. They often work closely with Partners and Directors.\n\n6. **Associate Director/Director**: Directors oversee multiple projects and teams, drive business development efforts, and develop long-term client relationships. They have a significant role in shaping the strategic direction of their practice area.\n\n7. **Principal/Partner**: At the top of the hierarchy, Principals and Partners are responsible for the overall success of the firm. They lead major client engagements, drive business growth, and set strategic priorities for their practice. They also play a key role in firm leadership and governance.\n\nThese titles reflect a typical progression within Deloitte Consulting, although specific titles and responsibilities may vary slightly across different service lines and practice areas within the firm.",
